==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ichthus
<hw>Ich"thus</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧k"th⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'ichqy`s</grk>.]</ety> <def>In early Christian and ecclesiastical
art, an emblematic fish, or the Greek word for <xex>fish</xex>, which
combined the initials of the Greek words <grk>Ihsoy^s</grk>,
<grk>Christo`s</grk>, <grk>Qeoy^ Gio`s</grk> <grk>Swth`r</grk>, Jesus,
Christ, Son of God, Savior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ichthyic</ent>⟦br⟧
